📘 Subject: General Studies Paper I (Prelims – Polity)
🧠 Topic: Fundamental Duties (Part IVA of the Constitution)

(Short topic but very important for Prelims.)

1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
🔹 What are Fundamental Duties?

Fundamental Duties are moral obligations of citizens towards the nation.

They remind citizens to:

Respect the Constitution

Promote harmony

Protect the country

📌 Mentioned in Part IVA (Article 51A)

🔵 Origin

Added by 42nd Constitutional Amendment Act, 1976

Based on Soviet Constitution

📌 Initially 10 duties → later 11 duties

🔹 11 Fundamental Duties (Simplified)

1️⃣ Respect Constitution, Flag & National Anthem
2️⃣ Follow ideals of freedom struggle
3️⃣ Protect sovereignty & unity
4️⃣ Defend the country
5️⃣ Promote harmony
6️⃣ Preserve culture & heritage
7️⃣ Protect environment
8️⃣ Develop scientific temper
9️⃣ Safeguard public property
🔟 Strive for excellence
1️⃣1️⃣ Provide education to children (added by 86th Amendment, 2002)

🔴 Important Points

Apply to citizens only

Non-justiciable (not enforceable by courts)

Parliament can make laws to enforce them

🔹 Importance

Promote discipline

Strengthen democracy

Encourage responsible citizenship

